      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="11.0" layoutY="40.0" prefHeight="300.0" prefWidth="380.0" text="Panels &#10;&#10;The left panel shows the system entities that are available. The add button above the panel can be used to add new system entities.&#10;The middle panel shows the concrete services that are available for the currently selected system entity, sorted by service registry. A green mark means the system entity workflow uses the service; a red mark means that the service is not used by the system entity workflow. The glasses symbols allow inspecting the service description as well as the service profile of each service and adapting the parameters dynamically.&#10;&#10;The right panel shows the definition of the workflow for the currently selected systen entity. Both a graphical representation and a specification with to the ReSeP workflow definition language are available.&#10;&#10;DTAS Configuration bar  &#10;&#10;The Open button allows opening a different set of available services.&#10;&#10;The Configure button allows dynamic configuration of the behavior of the underlying ReSeP platform. Message loss and communication delay can be defined, as well as the real time that matches with a logic time unit in the system. &#10;&#10;The Help button opens a window with the information you are reading now. &#10;&#10;The About button opens a window with general information about DTAS and a email address to contact the development team." wrapText="true" />
      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="10.0" layoutY="383.0" prefHeight="300.0" prefWidth="380.0" text="Panels&#10;&#10;The left panel shows the input profile that can be used to test the loaded configuration (i.e., system entities with available concrete services). The green triangle buttons on the right hand side are used to run the corresponding input profile (parallel runs are not supported). Clicking the red mark stops the execution of the running input profile.&#10;&#10;The right panel shows graphs with tables. This version of DTAS currently only supports one type of graph after an input profile ends. When the execution of the input profile completes, the results will be shown in the graphs and overview tables. &#10;&#10;DTAS Experimention bar  &#10;&#10;The Open button allows opening new input profiles (Open Profile item).&#10;&#10;The progress bar shows the progress of an ongoing execution of an input profile." wrapText="true" />
